<!-- ===== BUILDING YOUR OWN SETS ===== -->
<!-- 
  WORKFLOW:
  1. Traktor → Remix Deck Panel → New Remix Set
  2. Name: "Your Set Name"
  3. Drag samples from Browser → Slots 1-64
  4. Per-slot settings (right-click slot):
     - Volume: Set per-sample gain
     - Filter: HP/LP for tonal shaping
     - Color: Visual grouping (Drums=Red, Bass=Blue, FX=Yellow, Vox=Green)
     - Loop: ON for loops, OFF for one-shots
     - Sync: ON for tempo-synced loops
     - Reverse: Creative option
     - Gain: Match levels across set
  5. Page organization (8 slots per page):
     Page 1: Core Drums
     Page 2: Percussion
     Page 3: Bass/Melodic
     Page 4: FX/Transitions
     Page 5: Vocals/Hooks
     Page 6: Atmospheres
     Page 7: Fills/Rolls
     Page 8: Emergency/Utility
  6. Export: Gear Menu → Export Remix Set → "Your_Set_Name.remixset"
  7. Backup: Save .remixset files with your .tsi mappings
  
  SAMPLE SOURCES:
  - Native Instruments: Factory Library (free with Traktor)
  - Splice / Loopcloud: Subscription libraries
  - Sample Magic / Prime Loops: Genre-specific packs
  - Your own: Record from synths, vinyl, field recordings
  - Free: Cymatics, Vengeance free packs, Reddit r/drumkits
  
  NAMING CONVENTION (for quick browser search):
  [Category]_[Type]_[Key/Note]_[Length]_[Character]
  Examples:
  DRM_Kick_909_Short_Punchy
  PRK_Loop_128bpm_4bar_Driving
  FX_Sweep_Up_8bar_WhiteNoise
  VOX_Hook_Fmin_2bar_Female
  BAS_OneShot_C1_Sub_Deep
-->

<!-- ===== MAPPING INTEGRATION ===== -->
<!-- 
  Use with advanced-mapping.tsi M3 Layer:
  - M3 + Loop Encoder → Page Select (1-8)
  - M3 + Cue Pads 1-8 → Trigger Slots 1-8 (Current Page)
  - M3 + Shift + Cue Pads → Slot Mute Toggle
  - M3 + Shift + Loop Encoder → Slot Volume
  
  LED Feedback:
  - Pads 1-8: Slot Color (Red/Blue/Yellow/Green)
  - Pad Brightness: Volume level (Dim=Low, Bright=High)
  - Page Indicator: Encoder Ring LED (1-8 segments)
-->